LEVINE v. UNITED STATES. No. 1326,

Misc.

Decided June 20, 1966. George L. Saunders, Jr., for petitioner. Solicitor General Marshall, Assistant Attorney General Vinson, Beatrice Rosenberg and Kirby W. Patterson for the United States. Owen Rail for the Bar Association of the Seventh Federal Circuit, as amicus curiae, in support of the petition. Per Curiam.

The motion for leave to proceed in forma pauperis and the petition for a writ of certiorari are granted. The judgment is vacated and the case is remanded for a full hearing.
